def uint8(x):
    """custom uint8 - (if val < 0 then val = 0)"""
    x2 = np.copy(x)
    #x2[x2 < 0] = 0
    #x2[x2 > 255] = 255
    x2  = x2.clip(0, 255)
    return np.uint8(x2)

img = cv.imread(r"C:\Users\rom21\OneDrive\Desktop\LAB1\pyLAB1\saturn.png");
img = np.double(cv.cvtColor(img, cv.COLOR_BGR2GRAY))
m,n = img.shape
x1,y1 = np.meshgrid(np.arange(0, n), np.arange(0, m));
cx=(n)/2; cy=(m)/2;
X=(x1 - cx); Y=(y1 - cy);
R=X**2 + Y**2;
r1=20; r2=30;
LPF =  R <= r1**2;
HPF =  R >= r1**2;
BPF = (R >= r1**2) & (R <= r2**2);
BSF = (R <= r1**2) | (R >= r2**2);
imgfft=fft2(img);
imgfftshift=fftshift(imgfft);
imglpf=imgfftshift*np.double(LPF);
imghpf=imgfftshift*np.double(HPF);
imgbpf=imgfftshift*np.double(BPF);
imgbsf=imgfftshift*np.double(BSF);
lpfimg=ifft2(ifftshift(imglpf));
hpfimg=ifft2(ifftshift(imghpf));
bpfimg=ifft2(ifftshift(imgbpf));
bsfimg=ifft2(ifftshift(imgbsf));
deltalpf=img-np.double(np.real(lpfimg));
deltahpf=img-np.double(np.real(hpfimg));
deltabpf=img-np.double(np.real(bpfimg));
deltabsf=img-np.double(np.real(bsfimg));

2.5.1¶

using the frequency method we get an image of the same size as the original. using conv2d we get an image that is bigger by the length of the filter than the original. as we can see from the results of the delta images, the two methods provides the same results, the diffrence is very minor.

img = cv.imread(r"C:\Users\rom21\OneDrive\Desktop\image_lab3\cameraman.tif", 0)
n,m = img.shape
#hone = np.zeros(img.shape)
# hone[0:3,0:3]=np.array([[0,0,0],[0,1,0],[0,0,0]])
# hlpf = np.zeros(img.shape)
# hlpf[0:3,0:3]=(1/9)*np.ones((3,3))
# hhpf=hone-hlpf;
# sharp = np.zeros(img.shape)
# sharp[0:3,0:3]=1/9*np.array([[-1, -1, -1],[-1, 17, -1],[-1, -1, -1]])
# laplace = np.zeros(img.shape)
# laplace[0:3,0:3]=np.array([[0, -1, 0],[-1, 4, -1],[0, -1, 0]])
hone=np.array([[0,0,0],[0,1,0],[0,0,0]])
hlpf=(1/9)*np.ones((3,3))
hhpf=hone-hlpf;
sharp = 1/9*np.array([[-1, -1, -1],[-1, 17, -1],[-1, -1, -1]])
laplace = np.array([[0, -1, 0],[-1, 4, -1],[0, -1, 0]])

convlpf=signal.convolve2d(img,hlpf,'same');
convhpf=signal.convolve2d(img,hhpf,'same');
convsharp=signal.convolve2d(img,sharp,'same');

convlaplace=signal.convolve2d(img,laplace,'same');
convlpfValid=signal.convolve2d(img,hlpf,'valid')
convlpfSame=signal.convolve2d(img,hlpf,'same')

m,n=img.shape
m2,n2=hlpf.shape

# hlpf[m2:m+m2,n2:n2+n]=0
# hhpf[m2:m+m2,n2:n2+n]=0
# sharp[m2:m+m2,n2:n2+n]=0
# laplace[m2:m+m2,n2:n2+n-1]=0
# img[m:m+m2,n:m+n2]=0

hlpf = np.pad(hlpf,((0,m-3),(0,n-3)))
hhpf = np.pad(hhpf,((0,m-3),(0,n-3)))
sharp = np.pad(sharp,((0,m-3),(0,n-3)))
laplace = np.pad(laplace,((0,m-3),(0,n-3)))

hfft=fftshift(fft2(hlpf))
hfft2=fftshift(fft2(hhpf))
hfft3=fftshift(fft2(sharp))
hfft4=fftshift(fft2(laplace))
imgfft=fftshift(fft2(img))


newimg=imgfft*hfft
newimg2=imgfft*hfft2
newimg3=imgfft*hfft3
newimg4=imgfft*hfft4

shiftimg=ifft2(ifftshift(newimg))
shiftimg2=ifft2(ifftshift(newimg2))
shiftimg3=ifft2(ifftshift(newimg3))
shiftimg4=ifft2(ifftshift(newimg4))

deltaLPF=convlpf-shiftimg
deltaHPF=convhpf-shiftimg2
deltaSharp=convsharp-shiftimg3
deltaLaplace=convlaplace-shiftimg4
